        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 9:38PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 938 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Palo Duro Canyon, or 14 miles east of Canyon. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Canyon, Lake Tanglewood, Mescalero Park, Palo Duro Canyon,
and Timbercreek Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
